WEBVTT

00:01.935 --> 00:03.521
<i>[mellow music]</i>

00:03.522 --> 00:05.065
Shit.

00:05.066 --> 00:06.736
What do you want for breakfast,
Care Bear?

00:06.737 --> 00:08.322
Pancakes.

00:08.323 --> 00:10.493
Mommy's not making pancakes.

00:10.494 --> 00:13.273
How about some applesauce?

00:14.671 --> 00:16.129
ALEX: Oops.

00:16.129 --> 00:18.760
[laughs] That's... honest mistake.

00:18.761 --> 00:21.187
I'm, uh, I'm very kissable.

00:21.212 --> 00:22.391
- Yep.
- Can we just...

00:22.392 --> 00:25.231
can we maybe not do this
in your pantry/panic room?

00:25.232 --> 00:26.943
Totally. Let's do it on a date.

00:26.944 --> 00:28.677
- Smooth.
- Think about it.

00:28.702 --> 00:30.992
We do everything backwards...
living together, sex, children.

00:30.993 --> 00:34.500
A date is just the next step
in our natural regression.

00:34.501 --> 00:37.088
- CARRIE: I'm hungry.
- Uh, yeah, I'm coming.

00:37.089 --> 00:38.675
Come on.

00:38.676 --> 00:40.386
If you don't like it,
I'll never ask again.

00:40.387 --> 00:41.847
For at least two weeks.

00:41.848 --> 00:43.935
Okay. You're not giving up, huh?

00:43.936 --> 00:45.981
Nope.

00:45.982 --> 00:48.026
Okay, fine.

00:48.027 --> 00:51.032
Just no beach bars,
craft beer, or Hootie.

00:51.033 --> 00:53.412
- Rae, I'm not a bro.
- You're a dad bro.

00:53.413 --> 00:55.917
That's what happens when bros have kids.

00:55.918 --> 00:58.923
[chuckles]

00:58.924 --> 01:05.938
