02:19.209 --> 02:21.337
Hi.

02:21.338 --> 02:22.758
Surprise.

02:22.759 --> 02:24.343
That is the word for when someone

02:24.344 --> 02:26.306
shows up at your door unexpectedly.

02:26.307 --> 02:27.851
Um, I got you this.

02:27.852 --> 02:29.855
It's stupid and small,

02:29.856 --> 02:33.195
which is coincidentally
how I feel right now.

02:33.196 --> 02:35.992
- How are things?
- A little busy at the moment.

02:35.993 --> 02:38.497
- Is that her?
- No, it's my ex-girlfriend.

02:38.498 --> 02:40.209
- HENRY: Why?
- I don't know.

02:40.210 --> 02:42.421
- HENRY: Is she tall?
- Uh, no.

02:42.422 --> 02:44.050
HENRY: How about skinny?
She's skinny, right?

02:44.051 --> 02:46.722
- TATHIANA: She's...
- Uh, what's going on in there?

02:46.723 --> 02:48.183
Our fit model is a no show,

02:48.184 --> 02:49.603
and we have a critique tomorrow,

02:49.604 --> 02:51.231
and Henry's about to have an aneurysm.

02:51.232 --> 02:52.651
HENRY: Fuck it. Does she have legs?

02:52.652 --> 02:54.487
If she has legs, I'll put her on a box.

02:54.488 --> 02:56.660
I can stand on a box.

03:04.717 --> 03:08.265
Pajama day. That's fun.

03:08.266 --> 03:10.770
I slept on your couch.

03:10.771 --> 03:12.774
- Leia and I are splitting up.
- Very funny.

03:12.775 --> 03:14.485
Hey, where do you take someone on a date

03:14.486 --> 03:15.947
when you actually care about them?

03:15.948 --> 03:17.366
This is all very new to me.

03:17.367 --> 03:18.995
We're going to see a mediator.

03:18.996 --> 03:20.915
Hopefully it'll be amicable.

03:20.916 --> 03:23.086
Wait, seriously?

03:23.087 --> 03:24.715
Oh.

03:24.716 --> 03:27.428
You two are the paradigm,
the pinnacle...

03:27.429 --> 03:29.808
[stammers] The... I can't
think of another p word.

03:29.809 --> 03:32.772
- But this feels wrong.
- Maybe it's right.

03:32.773 --> 03:34.483
We moved so quickly
that we didn't consider

03:34.484 --> 03:35.903
that we might have
wanted different things.

03:35.904 --> 03:37.489
So, what, you're just gonna

03:37.490 --> 03:39.243
find another woman
and have a child with her?

03:39.244 --> 03:40.955
Maybe. I don't know.

03:40.956 --> 03:42.374
Worked for you.

03:42.375 --> 03:45.380
- Leon.
- Oh, I'll be fine.

03:45.381 --> 03:48.512
Go on, enjoy your date.

03:48.513 --> 03:51.267
Take her somewhere that she likes.

03:51.268 --> 03:58.281
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:58.282 --> 04:00.745
- [device beeps]
- No breathing.

04:00.746 --> 04:03.501
You are one with the pin.

04:03.502 --> 04:06.632
One with the pin.

04:06.633 --> 04:09.387
Little breath in. Yes, there we go.

04:09.388 --> 04:12.059
And out.

04:12.060 --> 04:14.480
[exhales]

04:14.481 --> 04:17.277
This will work.

04:17.278 --> 04:19.031
I think that if we
pin in the back a little bit

04:19.031 --> 04:20.325
so that it's a little tighter.

04:20.326 --> 04:21.911
WOMAN: Absolutely. Yeah.

04:21.913 --> 04:24.125
The hardest thing will be shared assets.

04:24.126 --> 04:25.545
Receipts help.

04:25.546 --> 04:27.131
And if there are certain objects

04:27.132 --> 04:29.093
or pieces that you want, make it known.

04:29.094 --> 04:30.930
You don't wanna
move into your next place

04:30.931 --> 04:32.559
and realize you don't
have your favorite chair.

04:32.560 --> 04:34.103
I don't have a favorite chair.

04:34.104 --> 04:36.482
- Me neither.
- I have a favorite plant.

04:36.483 --> 04:38.028
You can keep the plant.

04:38.029 --> 04:39.447
TANYA: What about bank accounts?

04:39.448 --> 04:40.867
Anything in both your names?

04:40.868 --> 04:42.494
Just a checking account.

04:42.495 --> 04:44.123
TANYA: Cut it in half. Easy peasy.

04:44.124 --> 04:45.543
And you said no children?

04:45.544 --> 04:47.630
- No children.
- TANYA: Great.

04:47.631 --> 04:50.720
That makes this all
very easy... relatively.

04:50.721 --> 04:53.100
Pew, pew, pew, pew. Pew.

04:54.520 --> 04:57.567
- You guys heading out?
- Let the mystery date begin.

04:57.568 --> 04:59.946
It's gonna be fun. We'll have fun.

04:59.947 --> 05:02.451
There are kid snacks in
the pantry if she gets hungry,

05:02.452 --> 05:04.246
but she'll probably
just go down any minute.

05:04.247 --> 05:06.042
I let her run around the park off leash.

05:06.043 --> 05:08.631
Also, our phones
will be off for a few hours,

05:08.632 --> 05:11.595
- so if anything happens...
- We will handle it.

05:11.596 --> 05:13.139
I know, it's hard to believe,

05:13.140 --> 05:14.851
but there's actually
people walking around

05:14.852 --> 05:16.688
who were raised
before cell phones, right?

05:16.689 --> 05:19.068
Millions of them voted for Donald Trump.

05:19.069 --> 05:21.239
Actually, text me hourly updates.

05:21.240 --> 05:23.201
Okay, you. We're off.

05:23.202 --> 05:24.621
Bye. [smooches]

05:24.622 --> 05:26.207
Bye, love you.

05:26.208 --> 05:27.669
- Okay.
- All right.

05:27.670 --> 05:29.589
Have fun you two. You look adorable.

05:29.590 --> 05:31.425
Bye.

05:31.509 --> 05:34.244
- After you.
- RAE: [indistinct]

05:39.317 --> 05:40.736
So where are we going?

05:40.737 --> 05:43.449
Third Eye Blind show.

05:43.450 --> 05:45.788
Sister Hazel's opening.

05:45.789 --> 05:47.750
[chuckles]

05:47.751 --> 05:50.255
[laughs]

05:50.256 --> 05:53.386
[sighs] Ah. Okay.

05:53.387 --> 05:55.683
I'm glad we're doing this.

05:55.684 --> 05:58.522
Yeah, me too.

05:58.523 --> 06:01.320
[radio playing softly]

06:03.324 --> 06:05.202
Is she asleep?

06:05.203 --> 06:06.788
Mm-hmm.

06:06.789 --> 06:08.208
You know what I think we should do?

06:08.209 --> 06:09.753
What's that?

06:09.754 --> 06:11.965
I think that we should
raid Alex's wet bar...

06:11.966 --> 06:13.384
Mm-hmm.

06:13.385 --> 06:14.846
And then take ourselves a hot tub.

06:14.847 --> 06:16.892
- Ooh.
- Mm-hmm.

06:16.893 --> 06:19.522
- That's perfect.
- Yeah.

06:19.523 --> 06:22.110
I wanna go for a quick run,
then come back,

06:22.111 --> 06:23.697
soak my muscles in the tub.

06:23.698 --> 06:25.367
Wait, you're gonna go for a run?

06:25.368 --> 06:26.870
Yeah, it's Thursday.
I always run on Thursday.

06:26.871 --> 06:28.958
Isn't it sorta dark outside?

06:28.959 --> 06:31.003
And you don't really
know this neighborhood.

06:31.004 --> 06:32.840
The streets are very, very windy.

06:32.841 --> 06:35.345
It's the Hollywood Hills.
It's not Aleppo.

06:35.346 --> 06:37.224
- I think I'll be okay.
- What are you gonna do?

06:37.225 --> 06:38.644
- You gonna run in your jeans?
- [laughs]

06:38.645 --> 06:40.063
No, of course not.

06:40.064 --> 06:42.401
I have shorts and shoes in the car.

06:42.402 --> 06:43.821
I'll be fine.

06:43.822 --> 06:45.240
I'll be back before you know it, okay?

06:45.241 --> 06:48.247
- Okay.
- Fire up that tub.

06:52.631 --> 06:54.466
RAE: You hate horror movies.

06:54.467 --> 06:57.097
ALEX: Generally, yes, but you love them.

06:57.098 --> 06:58.684
And just this once,

06:58.685 --> 07:01.022
I'm willing to overlook
your questionable taste.

07:01.023 --> 07:04.319
And who knows? Maybe I'll like this one.

07:04.320 --> 07:06.365
World looks different every day, right?

07:06.366 --> 07:10.791
I mean, five years ago,
you were my Airbnb guest.

07:10.792 --> 07:12.210
It could've been anyone in the world,

07:12.211 --> 07:13.756
- but it was you.
- [soft chuckle]

07:13.757 --> 07:16.218
- Hey.
- Yeah?

07:16.219 --> 07:19.224
I'm really glad that we're a family,

07:19.225 --> 07:21.855
with our perfect little girl.

07:21.856 --> 07:23.734
What's that they say in "The Road"?

07:23.735 --> 07:26.155
"We're carrying the fire."

07:26.156 --> 07:29.162
I like that. "Carrying the fire."

07:32.628 --> 07:35.634
[sobs]

07:39.432 --> 07:41.561
[sniffs]

07:41.562 --> 07:43.231
I still think it's too much.
Make it thinner.

07:43.232 --> 07:45.193
I don't want it to dominate.

07:45.194 --> 07:46.905
[sewing machine whirring]
WOMAN: So maybe do it...

07:46.906 --> 07:50.161
Just do it like that.

07:50.162 --> 07:52.918
Oh, thanks.

07:54.755 --> 07:56.508
You don't have to stay.

07:56.509 --> 07:58.971
Well, he's gotta do a final fitting.

07:58.972 --> 08:00.850
Yeah, but he can do it on me.

08:00.851 --> 08:02.645
It's fine, really.

08:02.646 --> 08:04.774
I... I wanna be here.

08:04.775 --> 08:06.402
Why?

08:06.403 --> 08:09.032
I like standing in silence,

08:09.033 --> 08:11.746
playing out what I'm gonna say
to you as soon as we're alone.

08:11.747 --> 08:15.796
That's a long time to practice.

08:15.797 --> 08:18.969
It better be good.

08:18.970 --> 08:21.975
