10:33.321 --> 10:37.621
AL GREEN: ♪ How can you mend ♪

10:37.622 --> 10:41.921
♪ A broken heart ♪

10:41.922 --> 10:44.761
Wine or whiskey?

10:44.762 --> 10:47.307
AL GREEN: ♪ How can you stop the rain ♪

10:47.308 --> 10:50.481
Okay.

10:58.455 --> 11:01.293
Rae's in love with Jeff,

11:01.294 --> 11:06.011
and Jeff wanted them to move to Austin,

11:06.012 --> 11:10.646
and she freaked out,
which is why she slept with me,

11:10.647 --> 11:12.775
and now they aren't speaking,

11:12.776 --> 11:15.572
and she and I...

11:15.573 --> 11:17.993
are...

11:17.994 --> 11:20.331
I don't know what we are,
but it doesn't look good.

11:20.332 --> 11:22.001
You okay?

11:22.002 --> 11:25.091
I don't know.

11:25.092 --> 11:28.013
Are you angry?

11:28.014 --> 11:30.811
Surprisingly not angry.

11:30.812 --> 11:33.817
Anger would be the obvious emotion,

11:33.818 --> 11:35.529
but no.

11:35.530 --> 11:37.156
Okay.

11:37.157 --> 11:39.411
I'm definitely sad.

11:39.412 --> 11:42.375
[soft laugh]

11:42.376 --> 11:45.799
I'm really, really sad.

11:45.800 --> 11:47.845
Yeah, you can be sad.

11:47.846 --> 11:52.145
- [sighs]
- It's okay to be sad.

11:52.146 --> 11:55.777
- You know what's weird?
- Why don't you tell me?

11:55.778 --> 11:58.115
Like, I'm sad for me, obviously,

11:58.116 --> 12:01.873
because it's sad
when the person you love

12:01.874 --> 12:04.962
tells you they're in love
with someone else.

12:04.963 --> 12:07.467
But,

12:07.468 --> 12:10.724
I think I'm more sad for her,

12:10.725 --> 12:13.020
because she's in pain,

12:13.021 --> 12:15.859
and it's my fault.

12:15.860 --> 12:18.531
- It's not your fault.
- I could've just said nothing.

12:18.532 --> 12:21.453
I could've put those feelings
onto other relationships,

12:21.454 --> 12:23.625
until they went away, and I didn't.

12:23.626 --> 12:26.171
Well, sure, but would've
felt it every time you saw her.

12:26.172 --> 12:27.758
- You always would've wondered.
- Okay.

12:27.759 --> 12:30.012
But now I'm wondering
what happens to us,

12:30.013 --> 12:33.018
because this is the one
I couldn't fuck up,

12:33.019 --> 12:35.899
and...

12:35.900 --> 12:37.443
I fucked it up.

12:37.444 --> 12:39.322
You'll find a way.

12:39.323 --> 12:42.705
You always do.

12:42.706 --> 12:45.334
I don't know about that.

12:45.335 --> 12:47.213
How was your night?

12:47.214 --> 12:50.804
Not as eventful as yours... [sighs]

12:50.805 --> 12:52.808
You two have fun playing house?

12:52.809 --> 12:54.310
Where is John, by the way?

12:54.311 --> 12:55.939
He better not be going through my shit.

12:55.940 --> 12:58.946
- Oh, holy shit.
- What?

13:01.744 --> 13:04.289
[indistinct chatter]

13:04.290 --> 13:06.294
[indistinct PA announcements]

13:10.762 --> 13:14.267
Thank you.

13:14.268 --> 13:16.856
Hey!

13:16.857 --> 13:19.110
So I take this corner down the hill,

13:19.111 --> 13:22.450
and of course, the shoulder
is narrowed down to nothing.

13:22.451 --> 13:24.496
And I'm feeling good, you know?

13:24.497 --> 13:27.460
I'm pacing at 6:45. I'm running strong.

13:27.461 --> 13:31.343
So I make the push,
I try to burst out of the turn,

13:31.344 --> 13:33.598
and then all of a sudden, headlights.

13:33.599 --> 13:35.017
Mm.

13:35.018 --> 13:36.729
The guy was driving dead center.

13:36.730 --> 13:38.566
Oh, no.

13:38.567 --> 13:40.862
Probably bridge and tunnel,
lost on his way to Sunset.

13:40.863 --> 13:43.200
Anyway, I didn't have any time to think,

13:43.201 --> 13:45.705
so I just took a leap
off the side of the road,

13:45.706 --> 13:49.420
and I must've clipped
a rock or something.

13:49.421 --> 13:50.841
Oh, my God.

13:50.842 --> 13:53.220
When I woke up, I was in an ambulance.

13:53.221 --> 13:55.432
Honestly, I'm grateful
that they called it in,

13:55.433 --> 13:58.858
'cause I could...
I could still be out there.

14:00.110 --> 14:01.444
I knew it.

14:01.445 --> 14:03.407
I mean, these canyon roads at night...

14:03.408 --> 14:05.035
they're a real death trap.

14:05.036 --> 14:07.833
It was a freak accident for sure,

14:07.834 --> 14:09.670
but I guess we have to accept

14:09.671 --> 14:13.553
that some things are out of our control.

14:13.554 --> 14:15.264
But running in the dark,

14:15.265 --> 14:17.351
that's in your control though, right...

14:17.352 --> 14:19.314
I think it would've happened regardless.

14:19.315 --> 14:21.319
I think it was fate.

14:24.408 --> 14:26.036
Okay, so,

14:26.037 --> 14:28.248
how long do you have to stay here?

14:28.249 --> 14:31.004
We can go now. They discharged me.

14:31.005 --> 14:32.674
- They did?
- Yeah.

14:32.675 --> 14:35.095
Hey, is it okay
if we stay at my place tonight?

14:35.096 --> 14:38.435
I just really need to be in my bed,

14:38.436 --> 14:40.774
with you.

14:40.775 --> 14:42.694
Yeah, of course.

14:42.695 --> 14:45.492
Thanks... [groans]

14:50.179 --> 14:51.718
TATHIANA: Do you
feel ready for tomorrow?

14:51.743 --> 14:53.161
[scoffs] Not even close.

14:53.186 --> 14:56.573
[laughs] You are ready.

14:56.598 --> 14:59.394
Thank you, Laura.
You're a passable mannequin.

14:59.395 --> 15:01.399
LAURA: You're welcome.

15:04.488 --> 15:07.786
Wow. Did you hear that?

15:07.787 --> 15:10.165
"Passable mannequin."

15:10.166 --> 15:12.504
A new career path reveals itself.

15:12.505 --> 15:15.384
Yeah, put it on my resume
above "turnip polishing."

15:15.385 --> 15:16.971
[chuckles]

15:16.972 --> 15:18.725
I guess I should open this, huh?

15:18.726 --> 15:20.521
It's nothing.

15:24.278 --> 15:27.074
One more for the wall.

15:27.075 --> 15:28.704
[laughs softly]

15:32.210 --> 15:34.757
You could've texted or called.

15:34.758 --> 15:37.178
You didn't have to stand around all day.

15:37.179 --> 15:40.434
Text apologies aren't real apologies.

15:40.435 --> 15:43.649
So, yeah.

15:43.650 --> 15:45.319
I'm sorry.

15:45.320 --> 15:46.739
I just...

15:46.740 --> 15:50.663
I was really immature about everything.

15:50.664 --> 15:54.087
I reacted poorly and
I'd like to make it up to you.

15:54.088 --> 15:56.049
Can I take you to dinner?

15:56.050 --> 15:57.468
I'm seeing someone.

15:57.469 --> 16:00.307
It's early, but it's something.

16:00.308 --> 16:02.019
Oh, okay.

16:02.020 --> 16:05.275
But if you're okay with that,
I could do dinner...

16:05.276 --> 16:08.741
just maybe when it's not
six hours from a critique.

16:08.742 --> 16:11.580
[chuckles] Yeah, that would be great.

16:11.581 --> 16:13.626
- You sure?
- Totally.

16:13.627 --> 16:16.089
Just let me know when,

16:16.090 --> 16:19.011
and, uh, good luck tomorrow.

16:19.012 --> 16:20.974
Okay... [chuckles softly]

16:20.975 --> 16:24.272
<i>[mellow music]</i>

16:24.273 --> 16:27.403
- Okay, bye.
- Bye.

16:27.404 --> 16:31.119
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:31.120 --> 16:34.417
I don't wanna say I saw God or anything.

16:34.418 --> 16:37.966
That's too much, but I felt something

16:37.967 --> 16:39.385
while I was lying on the ground

16:39.386 --> 16:41.306
waiting for the ambulance to come.

16:41.307 --> 16:45.857
There was this spirit or this aura.

16:45.858 --> 16:48.486
It was just willing me to go on,

16:48.487 --> 16:50.157
endure.

16:50.158 --> 16:52.829
- Hey.
- Hey.

16:52.830 --> 16:55.710
- How'd you sleep?
- Great.

16:55.711 --> 16:58.173
Well, I'm sorry about the alarm.

16:58.174 --> 17:01.179
My head feels like Swiss cheese today.

17:01.180 --> 17:03.058
I'm gonna go out for a quick run,

17:03.059 --> 17:05.311
and then I'm thinking maybe
we could do a late breakfast.

17:05.313 --> 17:08.737
Oh, and don't worry...
I'll watch out for headlights.

17:10.365 --> 17:17.378
<i>♪ ♪</i>

17:20.260 --> 17:22.429
Hey.

17:22.430 --> 17:24.601
- Mommy.
- [laughs] Hi.

17:24.602 --> 17:26.814
You ready, Care Bear?

17:26.815 --> 17:28.986
- My jacket.
- Okay.

17:35.666 --> 17:37.670
[sighs softly]

17:41.093 --> 17:43.097
Hey.

17:51.865 --> 17:54.243
Let's go to Austin.

17:54.244 --> 17:56.582
[sniffs]

17:56.583 --> 17:59.588
[sobs quietly]

17:59.589 --> 18:01.925
<i>[gentle guitar music]</i>

18:01.926 --> 18:04.347
ALEX: Okay?

18:04.348 --> 18:11.320
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:43.259 --> 18:44.679
[horn chirps]

18:50.858 --> 18:52.484
Is Jeff here?

18:52.485 --> 18:54.657
[indistinct chatter]

19:00.961 --> 19:03.632
Hey, bud.

19:03.633 --> 19:05.803
Look, I know I'm the last
person you wanna see

19:05.804 --> 19:07.933
right now... [grunts]

19:09.352 --> 19:10.772
[hisses]

19:10.773 --> 19:12.191
[groans]

19:12.192 --> 19:14.196
[panting]

19:16.701 --> 19:19.121
Are we okay now?

19:19.122 --> 19:20.833
I think so.

19:20.834 --> 19:22.838
All right.

19:35.989 --> 19:38.994
<i>[mellow music]</i>

19:38.995 --> 19:44.965
<i>♪ ♪</i>

19:44.966 --> 19:46.467
Are you trying to hurt yourself,

19:46.468 --> 19:49.139
'cause that's what it feels like lately.

19:49.140 --> 19:52.605
LAURA: Agreed, you've been
acting particularly stupid.

19:52.606 --> 19:54.191
Huh.

19:54.192 --> 19:55.903
LEON: Well, it's better
than trying to drive

19:55.904 --> 19:57.615
into a bloody wall.

19:57.616 --> 20:00.496
Thank you all
for your unwavering support.

20:02.458 --> 20:05.965
It'll get good light there.

20:05.966 --> 20:09.388
Hey, at least we get a pity dinner.

20:09.389 --> 20:13.856
<i>♪ ♪</i>

20:13.857 --> 20:15.483
Hey, will you...

20:15.484 --> 20:17.655
- will you chop these for me?
- Oh.

20:17.656 --> 20:19.993
Thank you.

20:19.994 --> 20:21.622
How's John, by the way?

20:21.623 --> 20:23.499
He's good. He should be here soon.

20:23.500 --> 20:27.215
- I heard he almost died.
- Is that what he told you?

20:27.216 --> 20:29.638
Yeah, he posted this
weird Instagram story

20:29.639 --> 20:31.683
with a bunch of religious iconography.

20:31.684 --> 20:33.102
I'll pull it up for you.

20:33.103 --> 20:35.566
Oh, my God. He got four stitches.

20:35.567 --> 20:37.319
He didn't even spend a night
in the hospital.

20:37.320 --> 20:39.991
God, I'm gonna go insane. I really am.

20:39.992 --> 20:41.828
One of these days, I'm just gonna snap

20:41.829 --> 20:43.498
and I'm gonna go crazy and
you're gonna have to visit me

20:43.499 --> 20:45.879
in the asylum 'cause
God knows nobody else will.

20:47.841 --> 20:49.636
I'm just gonna...

20:49.637 --> 20:51.055
[package thuds, knife clatters]

20:51.056 --> 20:52.851
- I'm just gonna cut these.
- Okay.

20:55.687 --> 20:57.610
It... it was life-changing.

20:57.611 --> 20:59.945
- Life-changing?
- Absolutely.

21:00.032 --> 21:01.702
Honey, would you say
I'm someone who's generally

21:01.703 --> 21:03.831
in control of his life?

21:03.832 --> 21:05.793
I guess, I... - Exactly.

21:05.794 --> 21:07.295
I'm an answers guy.

21:07.296 --> 21:09.049
How much will it cost to remodel?

21:09.050 --> 21:11.805
What's our turnover rate?
It's my bread and butter.

21:11.806 --> 21:13.559
- Pun intended.
- Ha.

21:13.560 --> 21:14.978
Then something like this happens,

21:14.979 --> 21:17.734
and you're not in control,

21:17.735 --> 21:21.742
and there are no answers,
it starts to make you think.

21:21.743 --> 21:23.494
Excuse me.

21:23.495 --> 21:25.498
What...

21:25.499 --> 21:28.212
Oh, a cheese plate. Cool.

21:28.213 --> 21:32.012
What are we in control of?

21:32.013 --> 21:33.724
Anything?

21:33.725 --> 21:36.688
[soft music playing]

21:36.689 --> 21:39.068
Deep breaths.

21:39.069 --> 21:42.240
- Please, put me to work.
- We're basically ready.

21:42.241 --> 21:45.371
Oh, my God, Laura, this looks amazing!

21:45.372 --> 21:48.420
No, we'll see how it tastes.
I'm a little rusty.

21:51.218 --> 21:53.471
- Teach me your ways, daughter.
- [laughs]

21:53.472 --> 21:55.225
[doorbell rings]

21:55.226 --> 21:57.605
Um, will you
bring these out to the table?

21:57.606 --> 21:59.024
Yes.

21:59.025 --> 22:01.614
Hey. You got this.

22:03.075 --> 22:04.828
- Yes.
- Okay.

22:04.829 --> 22:10.380
♪ ♪

22:10.381 --> 22:11.675
- Hey.
- Hey.

22:11.676 --> 22:13.094
Hi.

22:13.095 --> 22:14.889
Mm, come in.

22:14.890 --> 22:16.685
Oh, this is intimate.

22:16.686 --> 22:19.106
Oh, well, um, you sort of
caught me off guard,

22:19.107 --> 22:20.818
and I didn't wanna miss my window.

22:20.819 --> 22:25.285
But hey, compared to them,
I'll seem totally sane.

22:25.286 --> 22:27.707
Tathiana, you remember Alex?

22:27.708 --> 22:29.502
Hi. Sorry about my face.

22:29.503 --> 22:31.088
Oh, nice to see you again.

22:31.089 --> 22:34.136
- This is Leon and his plant.
- TATHIANA: Hi.

22:34.137 --> 22:36.473
LAURA: And John is my mom's boyfriend.

22:36.474 --> 22:38.394
- Hi.
- Hi, perfect timing.

22:38.395 --> 22:41.358
We need a new perspective.
Just to catch you up,

22:41.359 --> 22:42.778
I got in a little bit
of a running accident.

22:42.779 --> 22:44.239
Hence the stitches.

22:44.240 --> 22:45.828
They're under here, I could show you...

22:45.853 --> 22:47.204
Okay, I think we're ready to eat.

22:47.205 --> 22:49.150
Mm, great.

22:49.500 --> 22:50.961
I'm so ready. Come on.

22:50.962 --> 22:52.673
- After you.
- Yeah, yeah, yeah.

22:52.674 --> 22:54.510
Oh, my god, this looks amazing.

22:54.511 --> 22:57.850
[all talking at once]

22:57.851 --> 23:00.063
So, uh, where was I?

23:00.064 --> 23:02.526
Uh, did I say I was running?

23:02.527 --> 23:04.238
- So, I was running...
- Sweetie.

23:04.239 --> 23:06.200
And there's a bit of a visibility issue.

23:06.201 --> 23:10.793
John, sweetie, I think we've
all heard enough of this story.

23:10.794 --> 23:12.672
You fell and you hit your head.

23:12.673 --> 23:15.678
But you're all better now,
and that's the important thing.

23:15.679 --> 23:18.182
Yay, so, let's, uh,

23:18.183 --> 23:20.144
now enjoy Laura's amazing dinner.

23:20.145 --> 23:21.731
LAURA: Let's start... uh, bread.

23:21.732 --> 23:24.195
- VALERIE: Yay...[laughs]
- LAURA: Mushroom mélange.

23:26.116 --> 23:28.327
How was your critique?

23:28.328 --> 23:30.164
Well, the dresses held together,

23:30.165 --> 23:31.793
- so that's something.
- Mm.

23:31.794 --> 23:33.462
Did Henry do okay?

23:33.463 --> 23:35.634
Henry got in a screaming
fight with the fit model,

23:35.635 --> 23:38.347
and they had to be physically separated.

23:38.348 --> 23:40.811
- Oh, wow.
- He says hi, though.

23:40.812 --> 23:43.232
- Tell him I say hi back.
- [cell phone buzzes]

23:43.233 --> 23:47.115
[softly] Oh, excuse me.

23:47.116 --> 23:49.202
- What's up?
- Um, nothing.

23:49.203 --> 23:51.916
Sorry.

23:51.917 --> 23:55.006
I may have to leave early.

23:55.007 --> 23:56.634
All good.

23:56.635 --> 23:58.639
- Okay.
- Yeah.

24:00.476 --> 24:03.022
Leon?

24:03.023 --> 24:05.861
It's gonna be okay.

24:05.862 --> 24:08.742
I know right now it feels not okay,

24:08.743 --> 24:11.497
but I think that's gonna pass.

24:11.498 --> 24:14.419
Thank you,

24:14.420 --> 24:16.634
but I don't know if that's true.

24:19.180 --> 24:21.142
Excuse me.

24:27.071 --> 24:28.573
[clears throat] Hey, Val.

24:28.574 --> 24:30.577
Can I... can I talk to you for a second?

24:30.578 --> 24:32.999
In private?

24:40.180 --> 24:43.185
The mushrooms are great.

24:43.186 --> 24:46.568
♪ ♪

24:46.569 --> 24:48.990
Earthy.

24:54.208 --> 24:58.299
I hit my head, and I'm better now?

24:58.300 --> 24:59.802
- What?
- That's what you said...

24:59.803 --> 25:02.182
that I hit my head, and I'm better now.

25:02.183 --> 25:03.852
Is that not how you would describe

25:03.853 --> 25:05.271
your current state of being?

25:05.272 --> 25:07.358
No. No, it's not.

25:07.359 --> 25:09.864
Do we need to go to the hospital?

25:09.865 --> 25:12.620
[scoffing]

25:12.621 --> 25:15.208
John, I don't know what
you expect from me right now.

25:15.209 --> 25:17.003
- A little empathy...
- Really?

25:17.004 --> 25:18.464
Would be nice... yeah.

25:18.465 --> 25:20.719
Instead of diminishing my experience.

25:20.720 --> 25:22.973
You had four stitches,

25:22.974 --> 25:24.977
and you went running the next morning.

25:24.978 --> 25:26.731
Wow.

25:26.732 --> 25:29.904
And I rushed to that hospital
in a state of panic

25:29.905 --> 25:32.033
after telling you
not to run in the dark.

25:32.034 --> 25:35.958
And when I got there,
you were hanging out,

25:35.959 --> 25:37.377
taking a selfie.

25:37.378 --> 25:41.051
I had a traumatic experience, okay?

25:41.052 --> 25:42.470
I don't know if it was technically

25:42.471 --> 25:44.140
a near-death experience,

25:44.141 --> 25:45.644
but it's the closest thing
I've ever had to one,

25:45.645 --> 25:47.815
and it affected me profoundly.

25:47.816 --> 25:50.821
And I'm doing my best
to share my emotions...

25:50.822 --> 25:52.365
- Mm-hmm.
- With you.

25:52.366 --> 25:54.119
The least you could do
is meet me halfway.

25:54.120 --> 25:56.123
- Meet you halfway?
- Yes.

25:56.124 --> 25:57.668
I don't think that's too much to ask.

25:57.669 --> 25:59.170
[laughs] Okay.

25:59.171 --> 26:00.591
And now you're laughing at me.

26:00.592 --> 26:02.010
No... [laughs]

26:02.011 --> 26:04.932
- What is that?
- [giggles]

26:04.933 --> 26:07.563
[knocking]

26:07.564 --> 26:10.234
Leon?

26:10.235 --> 26:13.324
- ALEX: Hi, Leia.
- Is he here?

26:13.325 --> 26:16.749
Oh, yeah. I think he's in his office...

26:19.045 --> 26:21.465
I'm not doing it, okay?

26:21.466 --> 26:23.052
All my life, I have been

26:23.053 --> 26:24.972
surrounded by people
who have given up on me,

26:24.973 --> 26:27.143
but you don't get to do that,
not like this.

26:27.144 --> 26:29.523
- Can we, uh, do this in the...
- I don't wanna have a baby.

26:29.524 --> 26:31.653
I wish that I did,
but right now, I don't.

26:31.654 --> 26:33.615
But also, everyone says when you hit 35,

26:33.616 --> 26:37.539
your biological clock
turns into Big Ben, so...

26:37.540 --> 26:38.958
Big Ben is silent now.

26:38.959 --> 26:40.879
Ugh, whatever.

26:40.880 --> 26:42.716
I have all of these new clients,

26:42.717 --> 26:45.972
and all of our friends that
need our emotional support,

26:45.973 --> 26:48.185
and all the alerts on our phone
that tell us every single time

26:48.186 --> 26:50.022
we auto-pay a bill we can barely afford.

26:50.023 --> 26:51.776
I don't know if
I'll ever hear the clock.

26:51.777 --> 26:55.659
Maybe. Or maybe I'll change my mind.

26:55.660 --> 26:58.540
I don't know, but I just need us

26:58.541 --> 27:01.336
to take this one day at a time.

27:01.337 --> 27:03.883
Please.

27:03.884 --> 27:06.096
I know you want a family,

27:06.097 --> 27:08.643
and I want you to have everything,

27:08.644 --> 27:11.984
but I need you to hang in with me, okay?

27:19.541 --> 27:22.462
We are a family.

27:22.463 --> 27:26.261
I love you. That's all that I know.

27:26.262 --> 27:28.641
I love you too.

27:28.642 --> 27:31.647
<i>[gentle music]</i>

27:31.648 --> 27:38.662
<i>♪ ♪</i>

27:39.789 --> 27:41.208
Do you want some food?

27:41.209 --> 27:44.380
[laughs, sobs] I do.

27:44.381 --> 27:47.261
- I really do.
- Okay.

27:47.262 --> 27:50.309
Um, there's some mushrooms
that are very, very tasty.

27:50.310 --> 27:51.729
[sniffs] Mushrooms?

27:51.730 --> 27:53.232
I know, but they're really good.

27:53.233 --> 27:55.027
[laughter]

27:55.028 --> 27:56.739
- She's gotta head out.
- All right, nice to see you.

27:56.740 --> 27:58.826
- Bye again, good to see you.
- Nice to meet you.

27:58.827 --> 28:00.412
- Bye.
- Bye.

28:00.413 --> 28:02.333
I didn't even know
you could do probiotics.

28:02.334 --> 28:05.089
- You do probiotics, exactly.
- You do them?

28:05.090 --> 28:06.676
You were not kidding. [laughs]

28:06.677 --> 28:08.638
We're an acquired taste.

28:08.639 --> 28:11.060
[chuckles]

28:13.314 --> 28:16.444
I liked it.

28:16.445 --> 28:18.950
And I liked eating your cooking again.

28:18.951 --> 28:22.248
Yeah, yeah.

28:22.249 --> 28:24.460
Um...

28:24.461 --> 28:26.924
Listen,

28:26.925 --> 28:28.761
I kinda do this thing

28:28.762 --> 28:32.686
where I cycle through people.

28:32.687 --> 28:36.192
Like, we dance to song,
and when the song ends,

28:36.193 --> 28:37.821
I move on.

28:37.822 --> 28:40.242
But...

28:40.243 --> 28:44.500
I really don't wanna do that with you.

28:44.501 --> 28:46.672
I want you in my life.

28:46.673 --> 28:50.288
And if that's as a friend,

28:50.723 --> 28:52.389
okay.

28:53.102 --> 28:56.818
But please don't be a stranger.

28:58.864 --> 29:01.201
Okay.

29:01.202 --> 29:03.956
- Okay.
- Okay.

29:03.957 --> 29:06.462
BOTH: Good night.

29:09.134 --> 29:11.471
[indistinct chatter]

29:11.472 --> 29:13.225
<i>[Van William's "Revolution"]</i>

29:13.226 --> 29:16.189
Let me help you? Let me
help you, help you with it.

29:16.190 --> 29:17.720
- I don't know.
- What?

29:17.777 --> 29:19.555
I don't know.

29:19.580 --> 29:21.742
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:21.743 --> 29:25.750
VAN: ♪ Lost my valentine ♪

29:25.751 --> 29:27.754
<i>♪ ♪</i>

29:27.755 --> 29:31.762
♪ You could never
keep my meaning straight ♪

29:31.763 --> 29:33.766
